 {
  coords 3919.579 385.713 5176.226
  m_sTitle "Situation"
  m_sTextData "<h2>Enemy Forces</h2>"\
  "Canadian forces have been dispatched to try and re-secure this mine. Our informants say their weapons teams have been pulled off the assault, so it's two light infantry platoons and a command unit. They appear to be light infantry, so no heavy weapons or vehicles."\
  ""\
  "<b>Most Likely Course of Action</b>"\
  "One platoon will act as a maneuver element while the other platoon acts as a BOF or backup platoon. They will choose one point of attack to focus their assault. "\
  ""\
  "<b>Most Dangerous Course of Action</b>"\
  "The two platoons conduct a dual assault, one focusing on the lower portion of the mine, the other focusing on the top of the mine, pincering any fighters in the center."\
  ""\
  "<h2>Friendly Forces</h2>"\
  "We are sepeartists. We have about 25 men total (maybe?). "\
  ""\
  "NOTE: There is a cave system that connects the lower portion of the mine to the upper portion."
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "GC_SEPARATIST"
  }
 }
 {
